HEADWORD: Water furrow
<hw>Wa"ter fur"row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>A deep
furrow for conducting water from the ground, and keeping the surface
soil dry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

